Sentencas: The influence of the area difference between the current collector and the thin-film-processed cathode on the performance evaluation of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is investigated Two 2 cm by 2 cm anode supported SOFCs with a I cm by I cm cathode (Cell-1.0) and a 1.5 cm by 1.5 cm cathode (Cell-2.25) are fabricated and the performances are measured in a button cell test set-up with a cathode current collection area of 1 cm by 1 cm.
Titulo: Influence of Current Collector and Cathode Area Discrepancy on Performance Evaluation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell with Thin-Film-Processed Cathode
